{{expand language|topic=|langcode=fr|otherarticle=Guide Hachette des Vins|date=September 2015}}
The '''''Guide Hachette des Vins''''' is a [[French wine]] buying guide published by [[Hachette (publisher)|Hachette]] Livre (Hachette Pratique). Its first edition was released in 1985.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|title=Le Guide Hachette des Vins : présentation et notation des vins|url=http://www.hachette-vins.com/guide-vins/actualite-vin/81/le-guide-hachette-des-vins-presentation-et-notation-des-vins|website=Hachettevins.com|publisher=Hachette Livre|accessdate=21 September 2015|language=French|date=12 August 2015}}</ref> It is [[France]]'s best-selling [[wine]] guide and one of France's oldest.<ref>{{cite web|title=Le Guide Hachette des Vins 2016 vient de paraître !|url=http://www.hachette-vins.com/guide-vins/actualite-vin/161/le-guide-hachette-des-vins-2016-vient-de-paraitre|website=Hachette Vins|publisher=Hachette Livre|accessdate=21 September 2015|language=French|date=2 September 2015}}</ref> The Guide Hachette des Vins is considered to be France' most authoritative guide and commonly referred to as the bible of the French wine industry.<ref>{{cite web|title=This Week's Tasting The 'Little' Champagne that Ranked with the Best|url=http://www.federalwine.com/Articles/Deutz-Champagnes|website=Federal Wine & Spirits|accessdate=21 September 2015|date=5 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Le Guide Hachette des Vins|url=http://www.wine-searcher.com/awards-20-le+guide+hachette+des+vins|website=Wine-searcher|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Face value: After the musketeer|url=http://www.economist.com/taxonomy/term/109?page=113|website=The Economist|accessdate=21 September 2015|date=20 March 2003}}</ref><ref name="auto1">{{cite web|title=Wine Critics and Competitions|url=http://www.bigredwine.co.uk/OP/Awards%20&%20citations.asp|website=Big Red Wine Company|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref><ref name="auto2">{{cite web|last1=Fiorina|first1=Tom|title=Bringing some ‘international’ taste to France’s wine ‘Bible’|url=http://www.thevineroute.com/uncategorized/frances-wine-bible/|website=The Vine Route|accessdate=21 September 2015|date=5 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Goode|first1=Jamie|title=Buying guides|url=http://www.wineanorak.com/buyb.htm|website=Wine Anorak|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>
==Blind tasting panels== The Guide Hachette uses [[blind tasting]] panels to evaluate wines by [[appellation]].<ref name="auto"/> Each year 40,000 wines are tasted blind and rated by experts.<ref name="auto"/><ref name="auto2"/>
No fee is required to submit samples.<ref name="auto3">{{cite book|editor1-last=Corson-Schneider|editor1-first=Séverine|editor2-last=Cuperly|editor2-first=Christine|editor3-last=de Lavaur|editor3-first=Juliette|title=Le Guide Hachette des Vins 2016|publisher=Hachette Livre|location=Vanves|isbn=9782013962643|pages=6|language=French|chapter=Le Guide Hachette des Vins: Mode d'Emploi}}</ref> Only the most recently bottled [[vintage]] is allowed to be submitted for blind tasting.<ref name="auto"/>
[[Wine tasting]]s are organized locally in each region between January and May.<ref name="auto"/> Blind tasting sessions composed of a panel wine professionals ([[enologist]]s, wine merchants, wine brokers, [[sommeliers]]) are organized with the Syndicat Viticole or Winegrower's Syndicate of each [[appellation]] present in the guide.<ref name="auto"/>
==Rating system== Each wine is rated on a scale of 0 to 5.<ref name="auto2"/><ref name="auto3"/> {| class="wikitable" |- ! Taster's grade !! Wine Quality !! Final [[wine rating|Wine Rating]] |- | 0 || Faulty wine || Eliminated |- | 1 || Poor or mediocre || Eliminated |- | 2 || Good || Commended (no stars) |- | 3 || Excellent || * |- | 4 || Remarkable || ** |- | 5 || Exceptional || *** |}
The top rated wines are subject to a second round of [[blind tasting]].<ref name="auto2"/> After the second tasting, the panel votes on one or two wines to receive ''Coup de Coeur'' [Judges' Favorite].<ref name="auto2"/> The ''Coup de Coeur'' is considered to be the highest recommendation.<ref name="auto1"/><ref>{{cite web|last1=isa|title=Coup de Coeur Guide Hachette des vins 2015 !!|url=http://www.domainedemaouries-boutique.com/index.php?post/2014/12/01/Coup-de-Coeur-Guide-Hachette-des-vins-2015|website=Domaine de Maouries|accessdate=21 September 2015|language=French|date=1 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=CRU CLISSON 2010 : coup de coeur au GUIDE HACHETTE 2015|url=http://www.domainedelepinay.com/actualites%20du%20domaine%20de%20l%20epinay.html|website=Domaine de l'Epinay|accessdate=21 September 2015|language=French}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Grand Ardèche blanc - Prix "Coup de Coeur" du Guide Hachette des Vins 2010|url=http://www.thiebaud.ch/modules/shop/detail.asp?ID=6548|website=Thiébaud|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=COUP DE COEUR POUR LE GUIDE HACHETTE|url=http://www.cave-bonnieux.com/blog_detail.php?id=35|website=Cave de Bonnieux|accessdate=21 September 2015}}</ref>
==Regions covered== The 2016 edition covers: {{div col|colwidth=30em}} * [[Alsace]] and [[Lorraine (region)|Lorraine]] * [[Beaujolais]] and Lyonnais * [[Bordeaux]] * [[Burgundy]] * [[Champagne]] * [[Jura (department)|Jura]], [[Savoie]], [[Bugey]] * [[Languedoc]] and [[Roussillon]] * [[Poitou]] and [[Charentes]] * [[Provence]] and [[Corsica]] * [[South West France (wine region)|South-west France]] * [[Loire Valley]] and Central * [[Rhône Valley]] * [[Vin de Pays]]/IGP ([[Indication géographique protégée]]) * [[Luxembourg]] {{div col end}}
