{{italic title}}
[[Image:1893 Illustrated Europe no133.png|thumb|right|''Illustrated Europe'' no.133-134]]
[[Image:Europaische Wanderbilder no33.png|thumb|right|''Europäische Wanderbilder'' no.33]]
'''''Illustrated Europe''''' was a series of travel [[guide book]]s to Europe published by Orell Fussli & Co. of [[Zürich]] and C. Smith & Son of London.<ref>{{citation |title=Catalogue of Maps, Globes, & Diagrams, Published by C. Smith & Son |year=c. 1900 |location=London |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3ElKAAAAYAAJ&pg=RA1-PA64 }}</ref> It also appeared in a German-language edition (''Europäische Wanderbilder'') and a French-language edition (''L'Europe illustré'').<ref>{{citation |work=Proceedings of the Royal Geographic Society |publisher=[[Royal Geographical Society]] |location=London |title=New Geographical Publications |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uPU0AQAAIAAJ&pg=PA777 |date=December 1887 |number=12 }}</ref> The guides described localities in Austria, Germany, Hungary, Italy, and Switzerland in the 1880s-1890s.

